p: The average number of cells observed in each image taken at 20× magnification was quantified to assess the effect of surface topography on the cells. In the case of IPS, an average of 115.82 ± 87.68 cells was observed in each image and for VITA CAD Temp, 99.70 ± 91.71 cells. According to the Student’s t-test, this difference was not statistically significant (t 35 = 0.544, p = 0.590).
